2. Create Material Requests (for purchase/transfer), now after creating material request according to my reason but my quetion is after creating material request for that i must i should/ must create purchase order or not ?


Ans. 

1Ô∏è‚É£ What is a ‚ÄúMaterial Request‚Äù in ERPNext?

A Material Request is just a request document ‚Äî it doesn‚Äôt actually buy or transfer anything yet.
It tells the system what materials you need, how much, and why.



There are different types of Material Requests:

| Type                  | Used For                                        | Typical Source                               |
| --------------------- | ----------------------------------------------- | -------------------------------------------- |
| **Purchase**          | You need to *buy* materials from a supplier     | When raw material is not in stock            |
| **Material Transfer** | You need to *move* materials between warehouses | When stock exists in another warehouse       |
| **Manufacture**       | You want to *make* finished goods               | Generated from Production Plan or Work Order |
| **Customer Provided** | Customer supplies materials                     | Used in subcontracting cases                 |



2Ô∏è‚É£ In the Production Plan context

When you click ‚ÄúCreate Material Request‚Äù from the Production Plan, ERPNext looks at your Stock Availability and automatically decides which type to create.

So if:
- The system finds stock not available, it creates Material Request (Purchase).
- If stock exists in another warehouse, it can create Material Request (Transfer).
- If it‚Äôs a make-to-order scenario, it can create Material Request (Manufacture).

3Ô∏è‚É£ When do you need to create a Purchase Order?
| Scenario                                    | Action                                                                                               |
| -----------------------------------------   | -----------------------------------------------------------------------------------                  |
| ‚ùå Raw materials already in same warehouse  | ‚û§ No **Purchase Order** ‚Äî directly make **Work Order**  ( directly make work order)                  |
| ‚öôÔ∏è Stock in another warehouse               | ‚û§ Create **Material Request (Transfer)** ‚Üí then **Stock Entry (Material Transfer)**                  |
| ‚úÖ No raw materials in any warehouse        | ‚û§ Create **Material Request (Purchase)** ‚Üí convert to **Purchase Order** ( running buying cycle )    |



----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------


3. complete cycle with different phase


PHASE 1: PLANNING STAGE (Deciding What to Produce)

Sales Order / Sales Forecast
            ‚Üì
     (Triggers Demand)
            ‚Üì
     Production Plan
            ‚Üì
     Material Request ( here you can do different things like create purchase order, stock entry, sometimes this is no need to do) - read last above table
            ‚Üì
     Creates ‚Üí Work Orders (for each item/sub-assembly)


üß† Goal: Figure out what, how much, and when to produce.


PHASE 2: PREPARATION STAGE (Defining the Recipe & Process)

Item (Finished + Raw)
      ‚Üì
Bill of Materials (BOM)
      ‚Üì
Operation ‚Üí Workstation Type ‚Üí Workstation
      ‚Üì
Routing (Process Sequence)
      



üß† Goal: Define what materials are needed and how the item will be made.
Item = Product or material definition
BOM = List of materials required for 1 finished unit
Routing = Step-by-step operations (linked to Workstations)
Operation / Workstation = Who and where the work happens



üîπ PHASE 3: EXECUTION STAGE (Actual Production Happens)

Work Order (Fetches BOM + Routing) - x` you must to creating Bom & Routing first
     ‚Üì
Material Transfer for Manufacture (Stock Entry)
     ‚Üì
(Job Cards auto-created per operation)
     ‚Üì
Job Cards (Operation tracking per Workstation)
     ‚Üì
Stock Entry (Manufacture)
     ‚Üì
(Finishes production) after completing all operation by creating Job card for each opearation


üß† Goal: Convert raw materials into finished goods.
Work Order = The main manufacturing command
Material Transfer for Manufacture = Moves raw materials to the shop floor
Job Cards = Tracks each operation (Cutting, Welding, etc.)
Stock Entry (Manufacture) = Consumes materials, creates finished goods




üîπ PHASE 4: POST-PRODUCTION STAGE (Finishing, Costing & Inventory) this is optional step.

Work Order (Completed)
      ‚Üì
Work Order Costing
      ‚Üì
(Combines Material + Operation + Overhead Cost)
      ‚Üì
Stock Ledger / GL Entries
      ‚Üì
(Quality Inspection - Optional)
      ‚Üì
Finished Goods Available for Sale


üß† Goal: Finalize costs, quality, and inventory valuation.



